Description: Oval handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join, gradual curve.. Clay fine pale buff; much small mica. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 80,10 Name Timolaos or Timoleos? Parallels: Antioch, Samos
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1580)
